[4] Maharashtra State
Date: 11 Jul 2006 03:33:59 -0400 (EDT)
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Moneycontrol.com, Mumbai, India, 11 Jul 2006 [edited]
<http://news.moneycontrol.com/india/newsarticle/stocksnews.php?autono=226287>

The viral epidemic Chikungunya, which spreads through mosquitoes, has been
reported in a few districts of Maharashtra, an official said.
"About 7-8 districts are affected with the disease but the number of cases
has declined from what was reported in April and May," State Health
Directorate chief P P Doke said.
He said in April and May, health officials recorded around 2000 cases a day
in the state, "but now we have reports of an average of 300 cases a day".
Doke said local health officials are telling people to clean vessels in
which they store water and to dry them properly before filling them, as
mosquitoes breed in stagnant water.
