[6] Gujarat State
Date: 11 Jul 2006 03:33:59 -0400 (EDT)
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Expressindia.com, New Delhi, India, 11th Jul 2006, [edited]
<http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=192236>

Chikungunya dominated the zero hour in the Ahmedabad Municipal
Corporation's (AMC) standing committee meet on Monday with Congress
alleging that the disease was spreading fast in certain eastern areas.
Following this, Municipal Commissioner I P Gautam instructed officials to
intensify efforts to control the spread of the disease.
Congress members claim that so far, 500 cases of chikungunya have been
reported from Saijupur ward, 270 from Naroda-Muthiya and 170 from
Thakkarbapanagar wards, besides around 300 cases from Nikol ward. However,
medical officer health Dr S P Kulkarni contested the claim later in the
day. "We fanned our teams to the areas mentioned and found that 15 cases
have been reported since July 5 while another 55 cases of joints pains were
reported," said Dr Kulkarni.
The cases being reported as chikungunya could be of simple fever, "because
we have confirmations from private doctors in these areas that they have
not come across any chikungunya cases," claimed Dr Kulkarni.
